I"i<p>Keeps track which locks are in your environment, their state and allows you to control them.</p>
<ul>
<li>Maintains a state per lock and a combined state <code>all_locks</code>.</li>
<li>Registers services <code>lock.lock</code>, <code>lock.unlock</code> and <code>lock.open</code> (unlatch) to control locks.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Services</h3>
<p>A lock integration provides the following services:</p>
<h4>Service <code>lock.lock</code></h4>
<p>Lock your door, the attribute should appear under a ‘data’ attribute for the service.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Service data attribute</th>
<th>Optional</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>entity_id</code></td>
<td>no</td>
<td>Entity of the relevant lock.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h5>Example</h5>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">action:
  service: lock.lock
  data:
    entity_id: lock.my_place
</code></pre>
<h4>Service <code>lock.unlock</code></h4>
<p>Unlock your door, the attribute should appear under a ‘data’ attribute for the service.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Service data attribute</th>
<th>Optional</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>entity_id</code></td>
<td>no</td>
<td>Entity of the relevant lock.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h5>Example</h5>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">action:
  service: lock.unlock
  data:
    entity_id: lock.my_place
</code></pre>
<h3>Use the services</h3>
<p>Go to the <strong>Developer Tools</strong>, then to <strong>Call Service</strong> in the frontend, and choose <code>lock.lock</code>, <code>lock.unlock</code> or <code>lock.open</code> from the list of available services (<strong>Services:</strong> on the left). Enter something like the sample below into the <strong>Service Data</strong> field and hit <strong>CALL SERVICE</strong>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{&quot;entity_id&quot;:&quot;lock.front_door&quot;}
</code></pre>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Service data attribute</th>
<th>Optional</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>entity_id</code></td>
<td>yes</td>
<td>Only act on specific lock. Else targets all.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
